    "He earned his doctor's degree in 1940, also at Leiden, with a dissertation on seventeenth-century representations in Dutch art of the Batavian revolt against the Romans, <em>Zeventiende-eeuwsche uitbeeldingen van den Bataafschen Opstand</em>.": [],
