    "In November 1940 Van de Waal, being Jewish, lost his position at the Leiden Prentenkabinet under the Nazi occupation of the Netherlands.": [],
    "In 1941 his monograph on Jan van Goyen appeared.": [],
    "From March 1943 until March 1945, he was interned in the camps of Barneveld and Westerbork, along with a great number of Dutch Jews, many of whom were subsequently transferred to the camps in the East.": [
